alex.mojaki.boxes.middleware.get

Interface GetMiddleware<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultValue, EnsureBounds, SymmetricMiddleware

    public interface GetMiddleware<T>
    A PowerBox can apply a list of these objects when a user calls PowerBox.get() to change the final value that is returned to the user.
    See Also:
    PowerBox.get(), PowerBox.addGetMiddleware(GetMiddleware[]), BoxFamily.addGetMiddleware(GetMiddleware[])

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T onGet(PowerBox<T> box, T originalValue, T currentValue)
      Return the given currentValue or some transformation of it.

    • Method Detail

      • onGet

        T onGet(PowerBox<T> box,
        T originalValue,
        T currentValue)
        Return the given currentValue or some transformation of it. Called during PowerBox.get() for zero or more of these objects before applying the list of GetObservers.
        Parameters:
        box - the PowerBox whose value is being obtained by get.
        originalValue - the value the box contained before any middleware was applied.
        currentValue - for the first middleware in the sequence, this is the same as originalValue. For subsequent middleware, this is the return value of the previous middleware.
        Returns:
        the final value to be returned to the user and the parameter finalValue in the GetObserver.onGet(PowerBox, Object, Object) method for any GetObservers this box has.
